## üîß Variable Axes ‚Äì Advanced Typographic Control

### Weight
- Controls stroke thickness
- Use lighter weight for body, bold for headlines
- Avoid extreme weights at small sizes

### Grade
- Adjusts optical weight *without* affecting layout
- Use negative grade in dark mode to reduce perceived heaviness

### Width
- Controls horizontal space per glyph
- Narrow = more characters per line
- Wide = expressive, but not for dense UIs

### Optical Size
- Match font optical size to actual font size
- E.g. small optical size for body text; large optical size for hero text
- Prevents detail loss or visual awkwardness

